cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.GT, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of enumerating minimal dominating sets in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in discrete mathematics.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category as the paper presents algorithms for solving the problem.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of the problem in different graph classes.
- cs.GT (Graph Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph classes defined by forbidding certain induced subgraphs.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with computational geometry, but some of the techniques used in the algorithms may be related to computational geometry.
